🎧 Wave Rider Audio System (v1.0)

Use sound to time, amplify, and stabilize your state

🧠 Why audio hits harder
	•	Rhythm → entrains breathing + heart rate
	•	Build/drop → gives you a predictable “rise window”
	•	Repetition → conditions your nervous system fast

After a few sessions, your brain starts:

“Oh—we’re here again” → state comes online faster

⸻

🔊 Track Structure (what to use)

You don’t need perfect songs—just this structure:

1. Warm / Intro (30–90 sec)
	•	low energy, minimal beat
👉 sets baseline

2. Build (30–90 sec)
	•	rhythm increases
👉 where you start the rise

3. Drop / Peak (15–45 sec)
	•	strongest energy
👉 where you amplify

4. Groove / Sustain (30–90 sec)
	•	steady rhythm
👉 where you hold + stabilize

⸻

⚙️ How to run it (step-by-step)

🎵 Intro → Baseline
	•	slow breath (4 / 6–8)
	•	relaxed body

Cue:

“clear… ready…”

⸻

🎵 Build → Rise
	•	switch to 4 / 4 breathing
	•	slight tension → release
	•	narrow attention

Cue:

“there… building…”

⸻

🎵 Pre-drop → Prime the peak
	•	slightly faster breath
	•	tiny body pulse

Cue:

“now… ready…”

⸻

🎵 Drop → Peak
	•	amplify 5–10% (don’t overshoot)
	•	micro-movement (sway, pulse)
	•	slight upward head tilt

Cue:

“that’s it…”

⸻

🎵 Groove → Stabilize
	•	breath slows (4 / 6–8)
	•	widen awareness slightly

Cue:

“steady…”

⸻

🎵 Next build → Re-ignite
	•	repeat cycle

Cue:

“again…”

⸻

🔁 Training Effect (this is the goal)

After ~5–10 sessions:
	•	you feel the rise before the drop hits
	•	your body syncs automatically
	•	eventually → you can run the loop without audio

👉 audio becomes optional

